UN health agencies have given stamp of approval for including male circumcision to fight spread of AIDS.
World Health Organization (WHO) and specialized agency UNAIDS declared that millions of lives could be saved if circumcision were widely and safely practiced.
AIDS is a pandemic in some southern African countries, like Malawi where AIDS has cut life expectancy to 36.
Health ministers from the Southern African Development Community are meeting to deal with AIDS and other serious health issues.
In related studies mothers are encouraged to exclusively breast feed infants for first 6 months to help prevent infants getting AIDS.
